                            <comment id="14115005" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 29 Aug 2014 08:07:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch lgtm and I agree that this is how it should work, but I slightly worry about the fact that it&apos;s a breaking change as existing trigger names will be considered case-sensitive (and will thus start requiring quoting). This probably doesn&apos;t justify not doing this, but maybe it&apos;s worth putting it in 2.1.0 (a breaking change might be more expected in a major than a minor) with a clear warning in the NEWS file? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14117556" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 1 Sep 2014 16:58:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 to this btw, but please include a warning in the NEWS file upon commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14117649" author="mishail" created="Mon, 1 Sep 2014 19:22:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed into 2.1.0 with WARNING in the NEWS file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
